Starz (stylized as Starz! from February 1994 to March 2005,[1] and STARZ since April 2016, pronounced "stars") is an American premium cable and satellite television network which serves as Starz Inc.'s flagship service. Starz's programming features theatrically released motion pictures and first-run original television series.
The headquarters of Starz, and its sister networks Starz Encore and MoviePlex, are located at the Meridian International Business Center complex in Englewood, Colorado.[2] Through March 31, 2016, Starz's programming was subscribed to approximately 24.0 million television households in the United States.[3]



